  "summary": "This Chinese cabbage recipe is a symphony of flavours, offering spicy, sweet, sour, and salty notes in every bite. Braised with soy sauce and black vinegar, the cabbage absorbs the robust and tangy elements, making it a standout dish. Perfect for stir-frying or serving as a main course, this recipe brings the essence of Chinese cuisine to your table. Pair it with steamed rice or noodles to soak up the delicious sauce, or add it to a hot pot for a comforting meal. Whether you're a fan of Sichuan peppercorns or the subtle heat of chilli crisp, this dish can be adjusted to suit your taste. Ideal for a quick dinner, the Chinese cabbage recipe can also be enhanced with green onions, garlic, and ginger for extra depth",
